        "eligibility": "Eligibility\nThe applicant should be a citizen of India.\nThe applicant should be a student from recognized universities in India or abroad.\nThe applicant should have secured at least 60% marks in the last degree or certificate examination.\nThe applicant should qualify as ANY ONE of the following - \n          a)   Completed education under 10+2+3 pattern of education i.e. students who have completed 15 years of formal education. \n          b)   Pursuing 3rd year in Business studies and Engineering in 10+2+3 pattern of education.\n          c)   Pursuing 4th or 5th year in the integrated degree course or dual degree of 10+2+5 pattern of education\n          d)   Completed 2nd year of Software Engineering in any IIT/NIT or 1st/ 2nd Year of Business Studies in any IIM/ recognized Management Institute.\nNOTE 1: Merely possessing minimum qualifications as above shall not guarantee Internship in the Department. Candidates having exposure in the area of intended internship with good academic background and having higher qualification, based on need shall be given preference.\nNOTE 2: Students who have completed their education need not apply for the internship programme.\nNOTE 3: Depending on the number of applications received against a particular domain/area, the Department reserves the right to fix up the eligibility criteria."
