        "benefits": "Benefits\nBenefits\nOld people can improve their financial condition by taking advantage of this scheme.\nThe BPL beneficiaries of the state who are destitute old people will be provided with the benefit of this scheme.\nOlder people will not have to depend on others to live their life.\nUttrakhand Vridhawstha Pension Yojana Under this, people who are 60 to 79 years old are given a pension of Rs 200 from the central government and Rs 1300 from the state government i.e., Rs 1500.\nSimilarly, a total pension of Rs 1500 (Rs 500/- per month by the Central Government and Rs 1000/- per month by the State Government) is given to BPL beneficiaries above the age of 80 years. This scheme is like a support for the old people of the state.",
        "eligibility": "Eligibility\nEligibility \nThe applicant should be a permanent resident of Uttarakhand.\nOnly people who are 60 years or more of the state can apply for this scheme.\nThe beneficiary should be from a BPL family or his monthly income should not exceed Rs.4000.\nThe beneficiary whose son or son is more than 20 years of age but the candidate is living below the poverty line is eligible for this scheme.\nThe beneficiary over 60 years of age but not belong to a BPL family will be given the entire pension amount by the state government."
