    {
        "sr_no": "1283",
        "name": "Scholarship For Differently Abled Person",
        "link": "https://www.myscheme.gov.in/schemes/sfdap",
        "details": "Details\nThe Department of Empowerment of Persons with Disabilities, functioning under the Government of India, has taken a proactive approach to address the educational needs of students with disabilities. To this end, they have implemented three Scholarship Schemes: Pre-matric, Post-matric, and Scholarship for Top Class Education. These schemes have been designed with the overarching goal of empowering students with disabilities through education, recognizing the transformative power it holds in their lives.\n\nThe Pre-matric Scholarship Scheme aims to provide financial assistance to students with disabilities studying in classes 9 and 10. By extending support at the pre-matric level, the scheme aims to create an inclusive learning environment for these students and ensure that they do not face any financial barriers in pursuing their education.\n\nThe Post-matric Scholarship Scheme targets students with disabilities who are pursuing higher education, such as undergraduate and postgraduate courses. Recognizing the importance of continued education for their overall development and future prospects, this scheme provides financial support to cover various educational expenses, including tuition fees, books, study materials, and living expenses.\n\nThe Scholarship for Top Class Education is a prestigious scheme that focuses on providing assistance to students with disabilities who are pursuing professional and technical courses at the graduate and postgraduate levels. This scheme not only offers financial aid for educational expenses but also provides support for the purchase of necessary aids and assistive devices, such as computers, to facilitate the learning process.",
        "benefits": "Benefits\nFinancial Assistance: Scholarship of Rs. 50,000 or more than Rs. 50,000 to eligible students to cover various educational expenses, including tuition fees, books, study materials, and living expenses. This financial assistance relieves the financial burden on students and their families, enabling them to pursue their education without worrying about financial constraints.\nInclusive Education: The schemes promote inclusive education by offering scholarships at different educational levels, from pre-matric to postgraduate and professional courses. They ensure that students with disabilities have equal opportunities to access quality education, participate in mainstream educational institutions, and integrate into the larger student community.\nEmpowerment through Education: These schemes aim to empower students with disabilities through education. By providing financial support and removing barriers to education, the schemes enable students to gain knowledge, develop skills, and enhance their overall capabilities. This empowerment opens doors to better employment prospects, economic independence, and improved quality of life",
        "eligibility": "Eligibility\nHe/she should be a citizen of India\nA person with a disability having not less than 40% disability and having a disability issued by any competent medical authority.\nNot more than two disabled children of the same parents will be entitled to receive the benefits of the scheme. Provided in case the second child is a twin, the scholarship under this scheme will be admissible to both twins.\nScholarship for studying in any class will be available for only one year. If a student has to repeat a class, he/she would not get a scholarship for that class for a second (or subsequent) year.\nA scholarship holder under this scheme will not hold any other scholarship/stipend. If awarded any other scholarship/stipend, the student can exercise his/her option for either of the two scholarships/stipends, which is more beneficial to him/her, and should inform the awarding authority through the Head of the Institution about the option made. "
