        "eligibility": "Eligibility\nThe applicant should be a native and resident of Kerala State.\nWidowed/legally divorced/ wives abandoned by husbands are eligible to apply under this scheme.\nThe mothers of PwDs covered under the National Trust Act (NTA) will be eligible to apply under this scheme.\nThe applicants should belong to Below Poverty Line (BPL) category and do not have a source of steady income.\nThe beneficiaries must possess a valid 3-wheeler license.\nThe age limit of the applicant has to be 55 years or below.\nNote 01: The tax and insurance for the vehicles will have to be borne by the beneficiary.\nNote 02: The vehicle must be registered solely in the name of the beneficiary and the vehicle ownership cannot be transferred or sold."
